  "text": "From now on, we can investigate the noise error contributions for these Jacobi estimators. Mainly the Bienaymé-Chebyshev inequality is used to give two error bounds for these errors. Let us denote the noise error contributions for the Jacobi estimators e μ,κ ,βT,N,ξ (t 0 ) (see [CITATION_1] ) by e βT (t 0 ), then for any real number γ > 0",
